<br>
I do not care what anyone thinks of the roleplaying on this server, because that is what this server is for.  I wasn't very big on it when I started, mainly because I wanted to find out what it was about and how people did it here.  Once I figured it out and learned about the factions were and all of that, I was able to begin roleplaying.<br>
<br>
This past weekend, I went to the Maryland Rennaissance Festival and let me tell you that it was very neat.  People were dressed up and speaking as a fantasy/medieval person might speak.  I saw elves, minatours, barbarians, royalty, wenches, sword fights, kings chess (with real people) and bought a really neat amulet that reminds me of my character.  I told my friends that I felt as though I was walking around the world of Norrath.  Everything was so interesting and I highly recommend that anyone who lives around DC attend this fair.  <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.rennfest.com" target="top">www.rennfest.com</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
I have a whole new appreciation for this game after going to that.  We do live in a unique world on EQ.  Why not really become a part of it and leave this crazy world that we live in behind for a few hours?  I love the escape that is EverQuest.<br>
<br>
How about you?<br>
